cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.MM, cs.SI, cs.DC 

This paper is likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category as it focuses on mobile network performance measurement and uses the VpnService API on Android to intercept network traffic. It could also belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category as it discusses the importance of understanding mobile user experience and problem diagnosis. Additionally, it could be categorized under Multimedia (cs.MM) as it mentions measuring bandwidth cost and data usage. The paper also touches on System and Information Theory (cs.SI) as it discusses the accuracy of the measurement results. Finally, it could be classified under Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) as it uses a passive-active approach to monitor network performance on unrooted smartphones.
